# SVG → Icon Component Conversion

> **STOP: Before writing any icon `.tsx` file manually, run `@svgr/cli` first.**

## Step 1 — Run the CLI (always do this first)

For single-color icons (replace fill with `color` prop):
```sh
npx @svgr/cli --native --typescript --no-dimensions --expand-props end --replace-attr-values "#000000=currentColor" -- path/to/icon.svg > src/components/icons/MyIcon.tsx
```

For brand/logo icons with hardcoded colors (Spotify, PayPal, Notion — do NOT replace fills):
```sh
npx @svgr/cli --native --typescript --no-dimensions --expand-props end -- path/to/icon.svg > src/components/icons/MyIcon.tsx
```

## Step 2 — Fix the generated file (always required)

1. **Import** — replace any generated `SvgProps` import with `import type { IconProps } from "./types"`
2. **Props** — change signature to `({ size = 16, color = "currentColor", ...props }: IconProps)`
3. **Size** — add `width={size} height={size}` back on root `<Svg>` (`--no-dimensions` removes them)
4. **ClipPath IDs** — shorten verbose Figma IDs (e.g. `clip0_14508_8231` → `myicon_clip`) to avoid collisions
5. **Path data** — NEVER alter path `d` coordinates — even tiny changes break shapes

## Step 3 — Barrel export

Add to `src/components/icons/index.ts`:
```ts
export { MyIcon } from "./MyIcon"
```

## Standard shape all icons must conform to

```tsx
import Svg, { Path } from "react-native-svg"
import type { IconProps } from "./types"

export function MyIcon({ size = 16, color = "currentColor", ...props }: IconProps) {
  return (
    <Svg width={size} height={size} viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" {...props}>
      <Path d="..." fill={color} />
    </Svg>
  )
}
```

## Manual conversion — last resort only

Only if `@svgr/cli` is unavailable or crashes. Follow the same output shape above, and:
- Rename HTML attrs to JSX camelCase: `fill-rule` → `fillRule`, `clip-rule` → `clipRule`, `clip-path` → `clipPath`, `stroke-width` → `strokeWidth`
- NEVER rewrite or round path `d` coordinates
